<br>
That's another reason for the setup. We have had many anti-nuclear activists drop by but they don't hang around long. Generally they post a rabied flame post in Open Forum, full of ignorant suppositions which successfully puts our backs up. After a number of members have replied with hard facts, the angry visitor then gets embarassed or feels overwhelmingly outnumbered (or both). Either way they skidaddle. My creation of categories to keep ecowacky fearmongering away from more serious discussion also had the purpose of providing space for them to post as much as they want. Environment was designed especially for such topics as windmills and waste. It also broadened the topics available for discussion. You can discuss Albatross numbers, Whale hunting or anything else environmental there. <br>
It's still early days but imagine if one day we had 10 or 20 Yales's. Imagine what would happen to the board. A lot of people feel very strongly about the environment and hate nuclear power. Over at the Project Orion club we would be constantly repeating ourselves to newbies and it got very tiring. Most are ignoramuses but that doesn't change the fact we rarely swung any around to our point of view. They never stuck around long enough to absorb even the fundamental basis of our arguments. A friendlier category might have persuade them to stay on awhile and out of curiosity they might have listened in on other conversations around the board of a different nature. Those who became intrigued by the banter might have then felt inclined to delve more deeply into the concepts and ideas. A lot of ifs and buts I know but we are breaking new ground here remember. I was planning ahead for when our board grows to several times it's present size. Most boards die within months of creation but with determined members and patience a board can gradually grow into a membership of thousands of which hundreds are atleast semi-active participants. It takes time. The Project Orion club took years to become the number one largest science club at Yahoo. We are starting over from scratch but have a much better board layout. We shouldn't be complacent in how we plan ahead. We can avoid a lot of mistakes by learning from past experience painfully acquired at the predecessor club Project Orion. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uprojectorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>projectorion</A> at: 8/31/02 8:04:05 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/ulunarorbit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>lunarorbit</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.thespacerace.com/canflag.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Tourist</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(9/5/02 12:09